{"id":"datalinq-helper-jsfetchdata","name":null,"description":null,"code":"<div class=\"navbar\">\r\n  <div class=\"title\" id=\"function-title\"><a href=\"https://localhost:7277/datalinq/report/datalinq-guide@select-all-users@index\">DataLinq-Helper: JsFetchData</a></div>\r\n  <div style=\"width: 30px;\"></div> \r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"wrapper\">\r\n\r\n<button class=\"collapsible\">\r\n<span class=\"collapsible-label\">Basic usage</span>\r\n<span class=\"collapsible-actions\">\r\n<span class=\"action-button\" onclick=\"openPopup(event, 'jsFetchData_basic')\">Code/Query</span>\r\n</span>\r\n</button>\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n    @DLH.JsFetchData(id: \"datalinq-guide@select-surnames-where-firstname\", jsCallbackFuncName: \"basicUsage\")\r\n    <div id=\"basicUsage\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"description_jsFetchData_basic\" hidden>\r\nde: JsFetchData holt Daten von einer Abfrage und übergibt diese an eine JavaScript-Callback-Funktion. In diesem Beispiel werden die Nachnamen aus den erhaltenen Daten extrahiert und in einem div-Element angezeigt.\r\nen: JsFetchData fetches data from a query and passes it to a JavaScript callback function. In this example, the last names are extracted from the received data and displayed in a div element.\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"csharp_jsFetchData_basic\" hidden><script type=\"text/plain\">\r\n@@DLH.JsFetchData(id: \"datalinq-guide@select-surnames-where-firstname\", jsCallbackFuncName: \"basicUsage\")\r\n<div id=\"basicUsage\"></div>\r\n\r\n    JS: (in script-tag)\r\n    window.basicUsage = function(data) \r\n    {\r\n        const lastNames = data.map(item => item[\"LastName\"]).join(\", \");\r\n        document.getElementById(\"basicUsage\").textContent = lastNames;\r\n    }\r\n</script></div>\r\n<div id=\"sql_jsFetchData_basic\" hidden>SELECT DISTINCT LastName FROM Users</div>\r\n\r\n<button class=\"collapsible\">\r\n<span class=\"collapsible-label\">With filter</span>\r\n<span class=\"collapsible-actions\">\r\n<span class=\"action-button\" onclick=\"openPopup(event, 'jsFetchData_filter')\">Code/Query</span>\r\n</span>\r\n</button>\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n    @DLH.JsFetchData(id: \"datalinq-guide@select-surnames-where-firstname\", jsCallbackFuncName: \"withFilter\", filter: \"FirstName=Selina\")\r\n    <div id=\"withFilter\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"description_jsFetchData_filter\" hidden>\r\nde:JsFetchData mit dem filter-Parameter ermöglicht es, Filterkriterien an die Abfrage zu übergeben, um die abgerufenen Daten entsprechend zu filtern. \r\nIn diesem Beispiel wird nach dem Vornamen \"Selina\" gefiltert, und die entsprechenden Nachnamen werden dann in einem div-Element angezeigt.\r\nen:JsFetchData with the filter parameter allows you to pass filtering criteria to the query to filter the fetched data accordingly. \r\nIn this example, it filters by the first name \"Selina,\" and the corresponding last names are then displayed in a div element.\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"csharp_jsFetchData_filter\" hidden><script type=\"text/plain\">\r\n@@DLH.JsFetchData(id: \"datalinq-guide@select-surnames-where-firstname\", jsCallbackFuncName: \"withFilter\", filter: \"FirstName=Selina\")\r\n<div id=\"withFilter\"></div>\r\n\r\n    JS: (in script-tag)\r\n    window.withFilter = function(data) \r\n    {\r\n        const lastNames = data.map(item => item[\"LastName\"]).join(\", \");\r\n        document.getElementById(\"withFilter\").textContent = lastNames;\r\n    }\r\n</script></div>\r\n<div id=\"sql_jsFetchData_filter\" hidden>\r\nSELECT DISTINCT LastName\r\nFROM Users\r\n\r\n#if FirstName\r\n    WHERE FirstName = @@FirstName\r\n#endif\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<script>\r\n    window.basicUsage = function(data) \r\n    {\r\n        const lastNames = data.map(item => item[\"LastName\"]).join(\", \");\r\n        document.getElementById(\"basicUsage\").textContent = lastNames;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    window.withFilter = function(data) \r\n    {\r\n        const lastNames = data.map(item => item[\"LastName\"]).join(\", \");\r\n        document.getElementById(\"withFilter\").textContent = lastNames;\r\n    }\r\n</script>","created":"2025-04-15T07:59:23","changed":"2025-05-09T06:53:10.3035991Z","test_parameters":null,"included_js_libs":"legacy_chartjs"}